g2:c.FREE-TEXT.g2:a.TEXT: RELEASE NOTES This is GENSYMCID-1879, RT for GENSYMCID-933 BACKGROUND A Rule "Whenever item ...that is part-of receives a value" never executes even though it should when a value is receiving. in June 2012 Release. SOLUTION We used test kb and modified source so that the rule increments a parameter instead of posting a message. TESTING Test passes in HIP2016-09. We didn't test if the test fails in older versions. NOTES We had to insert "wait for 1 second" after causing an event which fires a rule to make sure parameter value is actually updated before we read it. It is understood that firing a rule after detecting an event is not an instant process. We believe that "Reducing the Number of Invocations per Firing" of g2refman.pdf is relevant to the problem, however we can't say we understand it completely, so this delay thing was partially a result of experiment and not a result of deep understanding. We believe it is acceptable this time because in test kb supplied with the CID operator should observe the results on the logbook and it is not specified when exactly the message would appear.

g2:c.RULE.g2:a.TEXT: whenever var-1 receives a value then conclude that var-2 = var-2 + 1
